alerts.title: Potential Domain Hijacking - company.biz
alerts.description:
The domain company.biz is pointing to unfamiliar IP addresses which do not appear within the IP ranges provided as assets.
This may indicate that the domain has been hijacked by cybercriminals, who altered the A records associated with the domain, resulting in the domain pointing to a different website such as a Phishing attack. Alternatively, the website may have been legitimately moved to a new hosting provider, a CDN (Content Distribution Network) may host company's website on a new location, or the domain has expired.
alerts.details:
The domain is pointing to 3 suspected IP addresses, the details of which are provided below.
%elements%Following is a current screenshot of the site.
alerts.recommendation:
We recommend investigating whether the suspected IP addresses associated with the domain are legitimately used by company or its service providers. If the IP addresses are unfamiliar, we recommend checking whether the domain has expired.
If the domain is still owned by company, but it is pointing to an unfamiliar IP address, we recommend investigating the site now pointed to by the domain to determine the nature and severity of the threat. If a threat is identified, it is recommended to contact the domain registrar.
The details of the hosting providers that control the IP addresses are also provided in the details above in the event you wish to attempt to takedown the site.

alerts.title: New Similar Domain - agentdiecompanyera.com
alerts.description:
IntelFinder has identified the domain agentdiecompanyera.com, which is similar to one of company's domains, company.co.

A website is associated with the domain. However, IntelFinder was unable to determine its nature.
alerts.details: %elements%Following is a current screenshot of the site:
alerts.recommendation:
We recommend investigating the contents of the website in order to determine its threat to company. If the website and/or domain are suspected to be associated with malicious activity targeting company, or if there is a violation of company's trademarks in any way, we recommend attempting to take both down.

The domain can be taken down by contacting its registrar, which can be contacted either by sending a takedown request by E-mail to abuse@godaddy.com, or by calling 480-624-2505. To take down the website associated with the domain, contact the web hosting provider either by sending a takedown request by E-mail to amzn-noc-contact@amazon.com and abuse@amazonaws.com, or by calling +1-206-555-0000.

If the takedown attempts of the domain are unsuccessful, you can try submitting a claim through ICANN's Uniform Domain Name Dispute Resolution Policy (more information available here).

If the domain is deemed suspicious, we also recommend to blacklisting it in any URL and mail filtering systems being used, to prevent employees from accessing it, or receiving Phishing letters that originate from it.
